esteid-browser-plugin 1.3.0 (2011-08-17)
========================================

This release adds support for pinpad smart card readers and switches to a new,
XML-based configuration file format. The required version of firebreath is now
1.5.

Plugin:
 - Various improvements to PIN dialogs
 - Support for pinpad smart card readers
 - Build with Firebreath 1.5
 - Switch to XML-based configuration files, with support for separate
   system-wide and user config files
 - Fixed a crash with parsing very long serial numbers used by the new
   esteid 2011 card
 - Misc. code cleanup

Mozilla extension:
 - Firefox 7, Thunderbird 7, SeaMonkey 2.4 compatibility

Many thanks to all the contributors:
Antti Andreimann, boamaod, Erkko Kebbinau, Kalev Lember, Sander Lepik.


esteid-browser-plugin 1.2.1 (2011-06-27)
========================================

Plugin:
- Added id.lhv.ee and www.politsei.ee to whitelist (Sander Lepik,
  Antti Andreimann)
- Fixed PIN2 dialog Cancel button handling to not send the PIN to card
  (Kalev Lember) (#133)
- Force boost filesystem version 2 to fix build with boost 1.46 (arc.mission)
  (#154)
- Don't display deprecated API warnings (Kalev Lember) (#116)

Mozilla extension:
- Firefox 5 and Thunderbird 5 compatibility (Kalev Lember)

Many thanks to all the contributors:
Sander Lepik, Antti Andreimann, Kalev Lember, arc.mission.


esteid-browser-plugin 1.2.0 (2010-11-04)
========================================

Plugin:
- Implement XMLSign emulation to support SEB and Nordea (Antti Andreimann)
- Implement application/x-digidoc emulation (Antti Andreimann)
- Initial i18n work (boamaod) (#110)
- Estonian translation corrections (Sander Lepik)
- Firebreath 1.3 support (Kalev Lember)
- Reworked CardService to stop polling when last plugin instance is destroyed (Kalev Lember)
- Register ActiveX control as preapproved (Kalev Lember) (#114)
- Expose personal data file properties in a separate JS object (Kalev Lember) (#124)
- Fixed Windows dialogs to show in IE 8.0 with protected mode on (Kalev Lember) (#116)

Mozilla extension:
- Do not load plugin into every browser window (Antti Andreimann)
- Firefox 4 compatibility fixes (Antti Andreimann)

Many thanks to all the contributors:
Antti Andreimann, boamaod, Kalev Lember, Sander Lepik.


